<p>Houston solar customers benefit from the federal Investment Tax Credit (ITC), which provides a 30% tax credit on the total system cost through 2032, then steps down to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034. Texas offers property tax exemptions for solar installations, meaning the added value to your home from solar panels won't increase your property tax burden. While CenterPoint Energy doesn't currently offer direct solar rebates, they do provide net metering programs that allow customers to sell excess energy back to the grid at retail rates. Additionally, Harris County and some municipalities offer expedited permitting processes for solar installations, reducing installation timeframes and associated costs for homeowners.</p>

